222 /*
223  Flags/methods for returning states.
224 
225  The SWIG conversion methods, as ConvertPtr, return an integer
226  that tells if the conversion was successful or not. And if not,
227  an error code can be returned (see swigerrors.swg for the codes).
228 
229  Use the following macros/flags to set or process the returning
230  states.
231 
232  In old versions of SWIG, code such as the following was usually written:
233 
234  if (SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags) != -1) {
235  // success code
236  } else {
237  //fail code
238  }
239 
240  Now you can be more explicit:
241 
242  int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,vptr,ty.flags);
243  if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
244  // success code
245  } else {
246  // fail code
247  }
248 
249  which is the same really, but now you can also do
250 
251  Type *ptr;
252  int res = SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj,(void **)(&ptr),ty.flags);
253  if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
254  // success code
255  if (SWIG_IsNewObj(res) {
256  ...
257  delete *ptr;
258  } else {
259  ...
260  }
261  } else {
262  // fail code
263  }
264 
265  I.e., now SWIG_ConvertPtr can return new objects and you can
266  identify the case and take care of the deallocation. Of course that
267  also requires SWIG_ConvertPtr to return new result values, such as
268 
269  int SWIG_ConvertPtr(obj, ptr,...) {
270  if (<obj is ok>) {
271  if (<need new object>) {
272  *ptr = <ptr to new allocated object>;
273  return SWIG_NEWOBJ;
274  } else {
275  *ptr = <ptr to old object>;
276  return SWIG_OLDOBJ;
277  }
278  } else {
279  return SWIG_BADOBJ;
280  }
281  }
282 
283  Of course, returning the plain '0(success)/-1(fail)' still works, but you can be
284  more explicit by returning SWIG_BADOBJ, SWIG_ERROR or any of the
285  SWIG errors code.
286 
287  Finally, if the SWIG_CASTRANK_MODE is enabled, the result code
288  allows to return the 'cast rank', for example, if you have this
289 
290  int food(double)
291  int fooi(int);
292 
293  and you call
294 
295  food(1) // cast rank '1' (1 -> 1.0)
296  fooi(1) // cast rank '0'
297 
298  just use the SWIG_AddCast()/SWIG_CheckState()
299 */
300 
301 #define SWIG_OK (0)
302 #define SWIG_ERROR (-1)
303 #define SWIG_IsOK(r) (r >= 0)
304 #define SWIG_ArgError(r) ((r != SWIG_ERROR) ? r : SWIG_TypeError)
305 
306 /* The CastRankLimit says how many bits are used for the cast rank */
307 #define SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT (1 << 8)
308 /* The NewMask denotes the object was created (using new/malloc) */
309 #define SWIG_NEWOBJMASK (SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT << 1)
310 /* The TmpMask is for in/out typemaps that use temporal objects */
311 #define SWIG_TMPOBJMASK (SWIG_NEWOBJMASK << 1)
312 /* Simple returning values */
313 #define SWIG_BADOBJ (SWIG_ERROR)
314 #define SWIG_OLDOBJ (SWIG_OK)
315 #define SWIG_NEWOBJ (SWIG_OK | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK)
316 #define SWIG_TMPOBJ (SWIG_OK | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK)
317 /* Check, add and del mask methods */
318 #define SWIG_AddNewMask(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
319 #define SWIG_DelNewMask(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_NEWOBJMASK) : r)
320 #define SWIG_IsNewObj(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_NEWOBJMASK))
321 #define SWIG_AddTmpMask(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r | SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
322 #define SWIG_DelTmpMask(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? (r & ~SWIG_TMPOBJMASK) : r)
323 #define SWIG_IsTmpObj(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) && (r & SWIG_TMPOBJMASK))
324 
325 /* Cast-Rank Mode */
326 #if defined(SWIG_CASTRANK_MODE)
327 # ifndef SWIG_TypeRank
328 # define SWIG_TypeRank unsigned long
329 # endif
330 # ifndef SWIG_MAXCASTRANK /* Default cast allowed */
331 # define SWIG_MAXCASTRANK (2)
332 # endif
333 # define SWIG_CASTRANKMASK ((SWIG_CASTRANKLIMIT) -1)
334 # define SWIG_CastRank(r) (r & SWIG_CASTRANKMASK)
335 SWIGINTERNINLINE int SWIG_AddCast(int r) {
336  return SWIG_IsOK(r) ? ((SWIG_CastRank(r) < SWIG_MAXCASTRANK) ? (r + 1) : SWIG_ERROR) : r;
337 }
338 SWIGINTERNINLINE int SWIG_CheckState(int r) {
339  return SWIG_IsOK(r) ? SWIG_CastRank(r) + 1 : 0;
340 }
341 #else /* no cast-rank mode */
342 # define SWIG_AddCast(r) (r)
343 # define SWIG_CheckState(r) (SWIG_IsOK(r) ? 1 : 0)
344 #endif

356 /* Structure to store information on one type */
357 typedef struct swig_type_info {
358  const char *name; /* mangled name of this type */
359  const char *str; /* human readable name of this type */
360  swig_dycast_func dcast; /* dynamic cast function down a hierarchy */
361  struct swig_cast_info *cast; /* linked list of types that can cast into this type */
362  void *clientdata; /* language specific type data */
363  int owndata; /* flag if the structure owns the clientdata */
364 } swig_type_info;
365 
366 /* Structure to store a type and conversion function used for casting */
367 typedef struct swig_cast_info {
368  swig_type_info *type; /* pointer to type that is equivalent to this type */
369  swig_converter_func converter; /* function to cast the void pointers */
370  struct swig_cast_info *next; /* pointer to next cast in linked list */
371  struct swig_cast_info *prev; /* pointer to the previous cast */
372 } swig_cast_info;
373 
374 /* Structure used to store module information
375  * Each module generates one structure like this, and the runtime collects
376  * all of these structures and stores them in a circularly linked list.*/
377 typedef struct swig_module_info {
378  swig_type_info **types; /* Array of pointers to swig_type_info structures that are in this module */
379  size_t size; /* Number of types in this module */
380  struct swig_module_info *next; /* Pointer to next element in circularly linked list */
381  swig_type_info **type_initial; /* Array of initially generated type structures */
382  swig_cast_info **cast_initial; /* Array of initially generated casting structures */
383  void *clientdata; /* Language specific module data */
384 } swig_module_info;

386 /*
387  Compare two type names skipping the space characters, therefore
388  "char*" == "char *" and "Class<int>" == "Class<int >", etc.
389 
390  Return 0 when the two name types are equivalent, as in
391  strncmp, but skipping ' '.
392 */
393 SWIGRUNTIME int
394 SWIG_TypeNameComp(const char *f1, const char *l1,
395  const char *f2, const char *l2) {
396  for (;(f1 != l1) && (f2 != l2); ++f1, ++f2) {
397  while ((*f1 == ' ') && (f1 != l1)) ++f1;
398  while ((*f2 == ' ') && (f2 != l2)) ++f2;
399  if (*f1 != *f2) return (*f1 > *f2) ? 1 : -1;
400  }
401  return (int)((l1 - f1) - (l2 - f2));
402 }
403 
404 /*
405  Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
406  Return 0 if equal, -1 if nb < tb, 1 if nb > tb
407 */
408 SWIGRUNTIME int
409 SWIG_TypeCmp(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
410  int equiv = 1;
411  const char* te = tb + strlen(tb);
412  const char* ne = nb;
413  while (equiv != 0 && *ne) {
414  for (nb = ne; *ne; ++ne) {
415  if (*ne == '|') break;
416  }
417  equiv = SWIG_TypeNameComp(nb, ne, tb, te);
418  if (*ne) ++ne;
419  }
420  return equiv;
421 }
422 
423 /*
424  Check type equivalence in a name list like <name1>|<name2>|...
425  Return 0 if not equal, 1 if equal
426 */
427 SWIGRUNTIME int
428 SWIG_TypeEquiv(const char *nb, const char *tb) {
429  return SWIG_TypeCmp(nb, tb) == 0 ? 1 : 0;
430 }

432 /*
433  Check the typename
434 */
435 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
436 SWIG_TypeCheck(const char *c, swig_type_info *ty) {
437  if (ty) {
438  swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
439  while (iter) {
440  if (strcmp(iter->type->name, c) == 0) {
441  if (iter == ty->cast)
442  return iter;
443  /* Move iter to the top of the linked list */
444  iter->prev->next = iter->next;
445  if (iter->next)
446  iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
447  iter->next = ty->cast;
448  iter->prev = 0;
449  if (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
450  ty->cast = iter;
451  return iter;
452  }
453  iter = iter->next;
454  }
455  }
456  return 0;
457 }

459 /*
460  Identical to SWIG_TypeCheck, except strcmp is replaced with a pointer comparison
461 */
462 SWIGRUNTIME swig_cast_info *
463 SWIG_TypeCheckStruct(swig_type_info *from, swig_type_info *ty) {
464  if (ty) {
465  swig_cast_info *iter = ty->cast;
466  while (iter) {
467  if (iter->type == from) {
468  if (iter == ty->cast)
469  return iter;
470  /* Move iter to the top of the linked list */
471  iter->prev->next = iter->next;
472  if (iter->next)
473  iter->next->prev = iter->prev;
474  iter->next = ty->cast;
475  iter->prev = 0;
476  if (ty->cast) ty->cast->prev = iter;
477  ty->cast = iter;
478  return iter;
479  }
480  iter = iter->next;
481  }
482  }
483  return 0;
484 }

486 /*
487  Cast a pointer up an inheritance hierarchy
488 */
489 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE void *
490 SWIG_TypeCast(swig_cast_info *ty, void *ptr, int *newmemory) {
491  return ((!ty) || (!ty->converter)) ? ptr : (*ty->converter)(ptr, newmemory);
492 }

494 /*
495  Dynamic pointer casting. Down an inheritance hierarchy
496 */
497 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
498 SWIG_TypeDynamicCast(swig_type_info *ty, void **ptr) {
499  swig_type_info *lastty = ty;
500  if (!ty || !ty->dcast) return ty;
501  while (ty && (ty->dcast)) {
502  ty = (*ty->dcast)(ptr);
503  if (ty) lastty = ty;
504  }
505  return lastty;
506 }

516 /*
517  Return the pretty name associated with this type,
518  that is an unmangled type name in a form presentable to the user.
519 */
520 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
521 SWIG_TypePrettyName(const swig_type_info *type) {
522  /* The "str" field contains the equivalent pretty names of the
523  type, separated by vertical-bar characters. We choose
524  to print the last name, as it is often (?) the most
525  specific. */
526  if (!type) return NULL;
527  if (type->str != NULL) {
528  const char *last_name = type->str;
529  const char *s;
530  for (s = type->str; *s; s++)
531  if (*s == '|') last_name = s+1;
532  return last_name;
533  }
534  else
535  return type->name;
536 }

538 /*
539  Set the clientdata field for a type
540 */
541 SWIGRUNTIME void
542 SWIG_TypeClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
543  swig_cast_info *cast = ti->cast;
544  /* if (ti->clientdata == clientdata) return; */
545  ti->clientdata = clientdata;
546 
547  while (cast) {
548  if (!cast->converter) {
549  swig_type_info *tc = cast->type;
550  if (!tc->clientdata) {
551  SWIG_TypeClientData(tc, clientdata);
552  }
553  }
554  cast = cast->next;
555  }
556 }
557 SWIGRUNTIME void
558 SWIG_TypeNewClientData(swig_type_info *ti, void *clientdata) {
559  SWIG_TypeClientData(ti, clientdata);
560  ti->owndata = 1;
561 }

563 /*
564  Search for a swig_type_info structure only by mangled name
565  Search is a O(log #types)
566 
567  We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.
568  Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
569  the circular list.
570 */
571 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
572 SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
573  swig_module_info *end,
574  const char *name) {
575  swig_module_info *iter = start;
576  do {
577  if (iter->size) {
578  size_t l = 0;
579  size_t r = iter->size - 1;
580  do {
581  /* since l+r >= 0, we can (>> 1) instead (/ 2) */
582  size_t i = (l + r) >> 1;
583  const char *iname = iter->types[i]->name;
584  if (iname) {
585  int compare = strcmp(name, iname);
586  if (compare == 0) {
587  return iter->types[i];
588  } else if (compare < 0) {
589  if (i) {
590  r = i - 1;
591  } else {
592  break;
593  }
594  } else if (compare > 0) {
595  l = i + 1;
596  }
597  } else {
598  break; /* should never happen */
599  }
600  } while (l <= r);
601  }
602  iter = iter->next;
603  } while (iter != end);
604  return 0;
605 }
606 
607 /*
608  Search for a swig_type_info structure for either a mangled name or a human readable name.
609  It first searches the mangled names of the types, which is a O(log #types)
610  If a type is not found it then searches the human readable names, which is O(#types).
611 
612  We start searching at module start, and finish searching when start == end.
613  Note: if start == end at the beginning of the function, we go all the way around
614  the circular list.
615 */
616 SWIGRUNTIME swig_type_info *
617 SWIG_TypeQueryModule(swig_module_info *start,
618  swig_module_info *end,
619  const char *name) {
620  /* STEP 1: Search the name field using binary search */
621  swig_type_info *ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(start, end, name);
622  if (ret) {
623  return ret;
624  } else {
625  /* STEP 2: If the type hasn't been found, do a complete search
626  of the str field (the human readable name) */
627  swig_module_info *iter = start;
628  do {
629  size_t i = 0;
630  for (; i < iter->size; ++i) {
631  if (iter->types[i]->str && (SWIG_TypeEquiv(iter->types[i]->str, name)))
632  return iter->types[i];
633  }
634  iter = iter->next;
635  } while (iter != end);
636  }
637 
638  /* neither found a match */
639  return 0;
640 }

642 /*
643  Pack binary data into a string
644 */
645 SWIGRUNTIME char *
646 SWIG_PackData(char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
647  static const char hex[17] = "0123456789abcdef";
648  const unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
649  const unsigned char *eu = u + sz;
650  for (; u != eu; ++u) {
651  unsigned char uu = *u;
652  *(c++) = hex[(uu & 0xf0) >> 4];
653  *(c++) = hex[uu & 0xf];
654  }
655  return c;
656 }
657 
658 /*
659  Unpack binary data from a string
660 */
661 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
662 SWIG_UnpackData(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz) {
663  unsigned char *u = (unsigned char *) ptr;
664  const unsigned char *eu = u + sz;
665  for (; u != eu; ++u) {
666  char d = *(c++);
667  unsigned char uu;
668  if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
669  uu = (unsigned char)((d - '0') << 4);
670  else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
671  uu = (unsigned char)((d - ('a'-10)) << 4);
672  else
673  return (char *) 0;
674  d = *(c++);
675  if ((d >= '0') && (d <= '9'))
676  uu |= (unsigned char)(d - '0');
677  else if ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f'))
678  uu |= (unsigned char)(d - ('a'-10));
679  else
680  return (char *) 0;
681  *u = uu;
682  }
683  return c;
684 }
685 
686 /*
687  Pack 'void *' into a string buffer.
688 */
689 SWIGRUNTIME char *
690 SWIG_PackVoidPtr(char *buff, void *ptr, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
691  char *r = buff;
692  if ((2*sizeof(void *) + 2) > bsz) return 0;
693  *(r++) = '_';
694  r = SWIG_PackData(r,&ptr,sizeof(void *));
695  if (strlen(name) + 1 > (bsz - (r - buff))) return 0;
696  strcpy(r,name);
697  return buff;
698 }
699 
700 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
701 SWIG_UnpackVoidPtr(const char *c, void **ptr, const char *name) {
702  if (*c != '_') {
703  if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
704  *ptr = (void *) 0;
705  return name;
706  } else {
707  return 0;
708  }
709  }
710  return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sizeof(void *));
711 }
712 
713 SWIGRUNTIME char *
714 SWIG_PackDataName(char *buff, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name, size_t bsz) {
715  char *r = buff;
716  size_t lname = (name ? strlen(name) : 0);
717  if ((2*sz + 2 + lname) > bsz) return 0;
718  *(r++) = '_';
719  r = SWIG_PackData(r,ptr,sz);
720  if (lname) {
721  strncpy(r,name,lname+1);
722  } else {
723  *r = 0;
724  }
725  return buff;
726 }
727 
728 SWIGRUNTIME const char *
729 SWIG_UnpackDataName(const char *c, void *ptr, size_t sz, const char *name) {
730  if (*c != '_') {
731  if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) {
732  memset(ptr,0,sz);
733  return name;
734  } else {
735  return 0;
736  }
737  }
738  return SWIG_UnpackData(++c,ptr,sz);
739 }

766 SWIGINTERN const char*
767 SWIG_Tcl_ErrorType(int code) {
768  const char* type = 0;
769  switch(code) {
770  case SWIG_MemoryError:
771  type = "MemoryError";
772  break;
773  case SWIG_IOError:
774  type = "IOError";
775  break;
776  case SWIG_RuntimeError:
777  type = "RuntimeError";
778  break;
779  case SWIG_IndexError:
780  type = "IndexError";
781  break;
782  case SWIG_TypeError:
783  type = "TypeError";
784  break;
785  case SWIG_DivisionByZero:
786  type = "ZeroDivisionError";
787  break;
788  case SWIG_OverflowError:
789  type = "OverflowError";
790  break;
791  case SWIG_SyntaxError:
792  type = "SyntaxError";
793  break;
794  case SWIG_ValueError:
795  type = "ValueError";
796  break;
797  case SWIG_SystemError:
798  type = "SystemError";
799  break;
800  case SWIG_AttributeError:
801  type = "AttributeError";
802  break;
803  default:
804  type = "RuntimeError";
805  }
806  return type;
807 }

1068 /* Convert a pointer value */
1069 SWIGRUNTIME int
1070 SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPtrFromString(Tcl_Interp *interp, const char *c, void **ptr, swig_type_info *ty, int flags) {
1071  swig_cast_info *tc;
1072  /* Pointer values must start with leading underscore */
1073  while (*c != '_') {
1074  *ptr = (void *) 0;
1075  if (strcmp(c,"NULL") == 0) return SWIG_OK;
1076 
1077  /* Empty string: not a pointer */
1078  if (*c == 0) return SWIG_ERROR;
1079 
1080  /* Hmmm. It could be an object name. */
1081 
1082  /* Check if this is a command at all. Prevents <c> cget -this */
1083  /* from being called when c is not a command, firing the unknown proc */
1084  if (Tcl_VarEval(interp,"info commands ", c, (char *) NULL) == TCL_OK) {
1085  Tcl_Obj *result = Tcl_GetObjResult(interp);
1086  if (*(Tcl_GetStringFromObj(result, NULL)) == 0) {
1087  /* It's not a command, so it can't be a pointer */
1088  Tcl_ResetResult(interp);
1089  return SWIG_ERROR;
1090  }
1091  } else {
1092  /* This will only fail if the argument is multiple words. */
1093  /* Multiple words are also not commands. */
1094  Tcl_ResetResult(interp);
1095  return SWIG_ERROR;
1096  }
1097 
1098  /* Check if this is really a SWIG pointer */
1099  if (Tcl_VarEval(interp,c," cget -this", (char *) NULL) != TCL_OK) {
1100  Tcl_ResetResult(interp);
1101  return SWIG_ERROR;
1102  }
1103 
1104  c = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(Tcl_GetObjResult(interp), NULL);
1105  }
1106 
1107  c++;
1108  c = SWIG_UnpackData(c,ptr,sizeof(void *));
1109  if (ty) {
1110  tc = c ? SWIG_TypeCheck(c,ty) : 0;
1111  if (!tc) {
1112  return SWIG_ERROR;
1113  }
1114  if (flags & SWIG_POINTER_DISOWN) {
1115  SWIG_Disown((void *) *ptr);
1116  }
1117  {
1118  int newmemory = 0;
1119  *ptr = SWIG_TypeCast(tc,(void *) *ptr,&newmemory);
1120  assert(!newmemory); /* newmemory handling not yet implemented */
1121  }
1122  }
1123  return SWIG_OK;
1124 }

1127 SWIGRUNTIMEINLINE int
1128 SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPtr(Tcl_Interp *interp, Tcl_Obj *oc, void **ptr, swig_type_info *ty, int flags) {
1129  return SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPtrFromString(interp, Tcl_GetStringFromObj(oc,NULL), ptr, ty, flags);
1130 }

1132 /* Convert a pointer value */
1133 SWIGRUNTIME char *
1134 SWIG_Tcl_PointerTypeFromString(char *c) {
1135  char d;
1136  /* Pointer values must start with leading underscore. NULL has no type */
1137  if (*c != '_') {
1138  return 0;
1139  }
1140  c++;
1141  /* Extract hex value from pointer */
1142  while ((d = *c)) {
1143  if (!(((d >= '0') && (d <= '9')) || ((d >= 'a') && (d <= 'f')))) break;
1144  c++;
1145  }
1146  return c;
1147 }

1149 /* Convert a packed value value */
1150 SWIGRUNTIME int
1151 SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPacked(Tcl_Interp *SWIGUNUSEDPARM(interp) , Tcl_Obj *obj, void *ptr, int sz, swig_type_info *ty) {
1152  swig_cast_info *tc;
1153  const char *c;
1154 
1155  if (!obj) goto type_error;
1156  c = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(obj,NULL);
1157  /* Pointer values must start with leading underscore */
1158  if (*c != '_') goto type_error;
1159  c++;
1160  c = SWIG_UnpackData(c,ptr,sz);
1161  if (ty) {
1162  tc = SWIG_TypeCheck(c,ty);
1163  if (!tc) goto type_error;
1164  }
1165  return SWIG_OK;
1166 
1167  type_error:
1168 
1169  return SWIG_ERROR;
1170 }

1173 /* Take a pointer and convert it to a string */

1175 SWIG_Tcl_MakePtr(char *c, void *ptr, swig_type_info *ty, int flags) {
1176  if (ptr) {
1177  *(c++) = '_';
1178  c = SWIG_PackData(c,&ptr,sizeof(void *));
1179  strcpy(c,ty->name);
1180  } else {
1181  strcpy(c,(char *)"NULL");
1182  }
1183  flags = 0;
1184 }

1197 SWIG_Tcl_NewPackedObj(void *ptr, int sz, swig_type_info *type) {

1200  if ((2*sz + 1 + strlen(type->name)) > 1000) return 0;
1201  *(r++) = '_';

1241 SWIGRUNTIME void
1242 SWIG_Tcl_ObjectDelete(ClientData clientData) {
1243  swig_instance *si = (swig_instance *) clientData;
1244  if ((si) && (si->destroy) && (SWIG_Disown(si->thisvalue))) {
1245  if (si->classptr->destructor) {
1246  (si->classptr->destructor)(si->thisvalue);
1247  }
1248  }
1249  Tcl_DecrRefCount(si->thisptr);
1250  free(si);
1251 }
1252 
1253 /* Function to invoke object methods given an instance */
1254 SWIGRUNTIME int
1255 SWIG_Tcl_MethodCommand(ClientData clientData, Tcl_Interp *interp, int objc, Tcl_Obj *CONST _objv[]) {
1256  char *method, *attrname;
1257  swig_instance *inst = (swig_instance *) clientData;
1258  swig_method *meth;
1259  swig_attribute *attr;
1260  Tcl_Obj *oldarg;
1261  Tcl_Obj **objv;
1262  int rcode;
1263  swig_class *cls;
1264  swig_class *cls_stack[64];
1265  int cls_stack_bi[64];
1266  int cls_stack_top = 0;
1267  int numconf = 2;
1268  int bi;
1269 
1270  objv = (Tcl_Obj **) _objv;
1271  if (objc < 2) {
1272  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "wrong # args.", TCL_STATIC);
1273  return TCL_ERROR;
1274  }
1275  method = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[1],NULL);
1276  if (strcmp(method,"-acquire") == 0) {
1277  inst->destroy = 1;
1278  SWIG_Acquire(inst->thisvalue);
1279  return TCL_OK;
1280  }
1281  if (strcmp(method,"-disown") == 0) {
1282  if (inst->destroy) {
1283  SWIG_Disown(inst->thisvalue);
1284  }
1285  inst->destroy = 0;
1286  return TCL_OK;
1287  }
1288  if (strcmp(method,"-delete") == 0) {
1289  Tcl_DeleteCommandFromToken(interp,inst->cmdtok);
1290  return TCL_OK;
1291  }
1292  cls_stack[cls_stack_top] = inst->classptr;
1293  cls_stack_bi[cls_stack_top] = -1;
1294  cls = inst->classptr;
1295  while (1) {
1296  Tcl_HashEntry* hashentry;
1297  bi = cls_stack_bi[cls_stack_top];
1298  cls = cls_stack[cls_stack_top];
1299  if (bi != -1) {
1300  if (!cls->bases[bi] && cls->base_names[bi]) {
1301  /* lookup and cache the base class */
1302  swig_type_info *info = SWIG_TypeQueryModule(cls->module, cls->module, cls->base_names[bi]);
1303  if (info) cls->bases[bi] = (swig_class *) info->clientdata;
1304  }
1305  cls = cls->bases[bi];
1306  if (cls) {
1307  cls_stack_bi[cls_stack_top]++;
1308  cls_stack_top++;
1309  cls_stack[cls_stack_top] = cls;
1310  cls_stack_bi[cls_stack_top] = -1;
1311  continue;
1312  }
1313  }
1314  if (!cls) {
1315  cls_stack_top--;
1316  if (cls_stack_top < 0) break;
1317  else continue;
1318  }
1319  cls_stack_bi[cls_stack_top]++;
1320 
1321  hashentry = Tcl_FindHashEntry(&(cls->hashtable), method);
1322  if (hashentry) {
1323  ClientData cd = Tcl_GetHashValue(hashentry);
1324  swig_wrapper method_wrapper = (swig_wrapper)cd;
1325  oldarg = objv[1];
1326  objv[1] = inst->thisptr;
1327  Tcl_IncrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1328  rcode = (method_wrapper)(clientData,interp,objc,objv);
1329  objv[1] = oldarg;
1330  Tcl_DecrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1331  return rcode;
1332  }
1333  /* Check class methods for a match */
1334  if (strcmp(method,"cget") == 0) {
1335  if (objc < 3) {
1336  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "wrong # args.", TCL_STATIC);
1337  return TCL_ERROR;
1338  }
1339  attrname = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[2],NULL);
1340  attr = cls->attributes;
1341  while (attr && attr->name) {
1342  if ((strcmp(attr->name, attrname) == 0) && (attr->getmethod)) {
1343  oldarg = objv[1];
1344  objv[1] = inst->thisptr;
1345  Tcl_IncrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1346  rcode = (*attr->getmethod)(clientData,interp,2, objv);
1347  objv[1] = oldarg;
1348  Tcl_DecrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1349  return rcode;
1350  }
1351  attr++;
1352  }
1353  if (strcmp(attrname, "-this") == 0) {
1354  Tcl_SetObjResult(interp, Tcl_DuplicateObj(inst->thisptr));
1355  return TCL_OK;
1356  }
1357  if (strcmp(attrname, "-thisown") == 0) {
1358  if (SWIG_Thisown(inst->thisvalue)) {
1359  Tcl_SetResult(interp,(char*)"1",TCL_STATIC);
1360  } else {
1361  Tcl_SetResult(interp,(char*)"0",TCL_STATIC);
1362  }
1363  return TCL_OK;
1364  }
1365  } else if (strcmp(method, "configure") == 0) {
1366  int i;
1367  if (objc < 4) {
1368  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "wrong # args.", TCL_STATIC);
1369  return TCL_ERROR;
1370  }
1371  i = 2;
1372  while (i < objc) {
1373  attrname = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[i],NULL);
1374  attr = cls->attributes;
1375  while (attr && attr->name) {
1376  if ((strcmp(attr->name, attrname) == 0) && (attr->setmethod)) {
1377  oldarg = objv[i];
1378  objv[i] = inst->thisptr;
1379  Tcl_IncrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1380  rcode = (*attr->setmethod)(clientData,interp,3, &objv[i-1]);
1381  objv[i] = oldarg;
1382  Tcl_DecrRefCount(inst->thisptr);
1383  if (rcode != TCL_OK) return rcode;
1384  numconf += 2;
1385  }
1386  attr++;
1387  }
1388  i+=2;
1389  }
1390  }
1391  }
1392  if (strcmp(method,"configure") == 0) {
1393  if (numconf >= objc) {
1394  return TCL_OK;
1395  } else {
1396  Tcl_SetResult(interp,(char *) "Invalid attribute name.", TCL_STATIC);
1397  return TCL_ERROR;
1398  }
1399  }
1400  if (strcmp(method,"cget") == 0) {
1401  Tcl_SetResult(interp,(char *) "Invalid attribute name.", TCL_STATIC);
1402  return TCL_ERROR;
1403  }
1404  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "Invalid method. Must be one of: configure cget -acquire -disown -delete", TCL_STATIC);
1405  cls = inst->classptr;
1406  bi = 0;
1407  while (cls) {
1408  meth = cls->methods;
1409  while (meth && meth->name) {
1410  char *cr = (char *) Tcl_GetStringResult(interp);
1411  size_t meth_len = strlen(meth->name);
1412  char* where = strchr(cr,':');
1413  while(where) {
1414  where = strstr(where, meth->name);
1415  if(where) {
1416  if(where[-1] == ' ' && (where[meth_len] == ' ' || where[meth_len]==0)) {
1417  break;
1418  } else {
1419  where++;
1420  }
1421  }
1422  }
1423 
1424  if (!where)
1425  Tcl_AppendElement(interp, (char *) meth->name);
1426  meth++;
1427  }
1428  cls = inst->classptr->bases[bi++];
1429  }
1430  return TCL_ERROR;
1431 }

1433 /* This function takes the current result and turns it into an object command */
1434 SWIGRUNTIME Tcl_Obj *
1435 SWIG_Tcl_NewInstanceObj(Tcl_Interp *interp, void *thisvalue, swig_type_info *type, int flags) {
1436  Tcl_Obj *robj = SWIG_NewPointerObj(thisvalue, type,0);
1437  /* Check to see if this pointer belongs to a class or not */
1438  if (thisvalue && (type->clientdata) && (interp)) {
1439  Tcl_CmdInfo ci;
1440  char *name;
1441  name = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(robj,NULL);
1442  if (!Tcl_GetCommandInfo(interp,name, &ci) || (flags)) {
1443  swig_instance *newinst = (swig_instance *) malloc(sizeof(swig_instance));
1444  newinst->thisptr = Tcl_DuplicateObj(robj);
1445  Tcl_IncrRefCount(newinst->thisptr);
1446  newinst->thisvalue = thisvalue;
1447  newinst->classptr = (swig_class *) type->clientdata;
1448  newinst->destroy = flags;
1449  newinst->cmdtok = Tcl_CreateObjCommand(interp, Tcl_GetStringFromObj(robj,NULL), (swig_wrapper_func) SWIG_MethodCommand, (ClientData) newinst, (swig_delete_func) SWIG_ObjectDelete);
1450  if (flags) {
1451  SWIG_Acquire(thisvalue);
1452  }
1453  }
1454  }
1455  return robj;
1456 }
1457 
1458 /* Function to create objects */
1459 SWIGRUNTIME int
1460 SWIG_Tcl_ObjectConstructor(ClientData clientData, Tcl_Interp *interp, int objc, Tcl_Obj *CONST objv[]) {
1461  Tcl_Obj *newObj = 0;
1462  void *thisvalue = 0;
1463  swig_instance *newinst = 0;
1464  swig_class *classptr = (swig_class *) clientData;
1465  swig_wrapper cons = 0;
1466  char *name = 0;
1467  int firstarg = 0;
1468  int thisarg = 0;
1469  int destroy = 1;
1470 
1471  if (!classptr) {
1472  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "swig: internal runtime error. No class object defined.", TCL_STATIC);
1473  return TCL_ERROR;
1474  }
1475  cons = classptr->constructor;
1476  if (objc > 1) {
1477  char *s = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[1],NULL);
1478  if (strcmp(s,"-this") == 0) {
1479  thisarg = 2;
1480  cons = 0;
1481  } else if (strcmp(s,"-args") == 0) {
1482  firstarg = 1;
1483  } else if (objc == 2) {
1484  firstarg = 1;
1485  name = s;
1486  } else if (objc >= 3) {
1487  char *s1;
1488  name = s;
1489  s1 = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[2],NULL);
1490  if (strcmp(s1,"-this") == 0) {
1491  thisarg = 3;
1492  cons = 0;
1493  } else {
1494  firstarg = 1;
1495  }
1496  }
1497  }
1498  if (cons) {
1499  int result;
1500  result = (*cons)(0, interp, objc-firstarg, &objv[firstarg]);
1501  if (result != TCL_OK) {
1502  return result;
1503  }
1504  newObj = Tcl_DuplicateObj(Tcl_GetObjResult(interp));
1505  if (!name) name = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(newObj,NULL);
1506  } else if (thisarg > 0) {
1507  if (thisarg < objc) {
1508  destroy = 0;
1509  newObj = Tcl_DuplicateObj(objv[thisarg]);
1510  if (!name) name = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(newObj,NULL);
1511  } else {
1512  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "wrong # args.", TCL_STATIC);
1513  return TCL_ERROR;
1514  }
1515  } else {
1516  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "No constructor available.", TCL_STATIC);
1517  return TCL_ERROR;
1518  }
1519  if (SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPtr(interp,newObj, (void **) &thisvalue, *(classptr->type), 0) != SWIG_OK) {
1520  Tcl_DecrRefCount(newObj);
1521  return TCL_ERROR;
1522  }
1523  newinst = (swig_instance *) malloc(sizeof(swig_instance));
1524  newinst->thisptr = newObj;
1525  Tcl_IncrRefCount(newObj);
1526  newinst->thisvalue = thisvalue;
1527  newinst->classptr = classptr;
1528  newinst->destroy = destroy;
1529  if (destroy) {
1530  SWIG_Acquire(thisvalue);
1531  }
1532  newinst->cmdtok = Tcl_CreateObjCommand(interp,name, (swig_wrapper) SWIG_MethodCommand, (ClientData) newinst, (swig_delete_func) SWIG_ObjectDelete);
1533  return TCL_OK;
1534 }

1536 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*
1537  * Get arguments
1538  * -----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/
1539 SWIGRUNTIME int
1540 SWIG_Tcl_GetArgs(Tcl_Interp *interp, int objc, Tcl_Obj *CONST objv[], const char *fmt, ...) {
1541  int argno = 0, opt = 0;
1542  long tempi;
1543  double tempd;
1544  const char *c;
1545  va_list ap;
1546  void *vptr;
1547  Tcl_Obj *obj = 0;
1548  swig_type_info *ty;
1549 
1550  va_start(ap,fmt);
1551  for (c = fmt; (*c && (*c != ':') && (*c != ';')); c++,argno++) {
1552  if (*c == '|') {
1553  opt = 1;
1554  c++;
1555  }
1556  if (argno >= (objc-1)) {
1557  if (!opt) {
1558  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "Wrong number of arguments ", TCL_STATIC);
1559  goto argerror;
1560  } else {
1561  va_end(ap);
1562  return TCL_OK;
1563  }
1564  }
1565 
1566  vptr = va_arg(ap,void *);
1567  if (vptr) {
1568  if (isupper(*c)) {
1569  obj = SWIG_Tcl_GetConstantObj(Tcl_GetStringFromObj(objv[argno+1],0));
1570  if (!obj) obj = objv[argno+1];
1571  } else {
1572  obj = objv[argno+1];
1573  }
1574  switch(*c) {
1575  case 'i': case 'I':
1576  case 'l': case 'L':
1577  case 'h': case 'H':
1578  case 'b': case 'B':
1579  if (Tcl_GetLongFromObj(interp,obj,&tempi) != TCL_OK) goto argerror;
1580  if ((*c == 'i') || (*c == 'I')) *((int *)vptr) = (int)tempi;
1581  else if ((*c == 'l') || (*c == 'L')) *((long *)vptr) = (long)tempi;
1582  else if ((*c == 'h') || (*c == 'H')) *((short*)vptr) = (short)tempi;
1583  else if ((*c == 'b') || (*c == 'B')) *((unsigned char *)vptr) = (unsigned char)tempi;
1584  break;
1585  case 'f': case 'F':
1586  case 'd': case 'D':
1587  if (Tcl_GetDoubleFromObj(interp,obj,&tempd) != TCL_OK) goto argerror;
1588  if ((*c == 'f') || (*c == 'F')) *((float *) vptr) = (float)tempd;
1589  else if ((*c == 'd') || (*c == 'D')) *((double*) vptr) = tempd;
1590  break;
1591  case 's': case 'S':
1592  if (*(c+1) == '#') {
1593  int *vlptr = (int *) va_arg(ap, void *);
1594  *((char **) vptr) = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(obj, vlptr);
1595  c++;
1596  } else {
1597  *((char **)vptr) = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(obj,NULL);
1598  }
1599  break;
1600  case 'c': case 'C':
1601  *((char *)vptr) = *(Tcl_GetStringFromObj(obj,NULL));
1602  break;
1603  case 'p': case 'P':
1604  ty = (swig_type_info *) va_arg(ap, void *);
1605  if (SWIG_Tcl_ConvertPtr(interp, obj, (void **) vptr, ty, 0) != SWIG_OK) goto argerror;
1606  break;
1607  case 'o': case 'O':
1608  *((Tcl_Obj **)vptr) = objv[argno+1];
1609  break;
1610  default:
1611  break;
1612  }
1613  }
1614  }
1615 
1616  if ((*c != ';') && ((objc-1) > argno)) {
1617  Tcl_SetResult(interp, (char *) "Wrong # args.", TCL_STATIC);
1618  goto argerror;
1619  }
1620  va_end(ap);
1621  return TCL_OK;
1622 
1623  argerror:
1624  {
1625  char temp[32];
1626  sprintf(temp,"%d", argno+1);
1627  c = strchr(fmt,':');
1628  if (!c) c = strchr(fmt,';');
1629  if (!c) c = (char *)"";
1630  Tcl_AppendResult(interp,c," argument ", temp, NULL);
1631  va_end(ap);
1632  return TCL_ERROR;
1633  }
1634 }

1637 }

1754 SWIGINTERN int
1755 SWIG_AsVal_unsigned_SS_long SWIG_TCL_DECL_ARGS_2(Tcl_Obj *obj, unsigned long *val) {
1756  long v;
1757  if (Tcl_GetLongFromObj(0,obj, &v) == TCL_OK) {
1758  if (v >= 0) {
1759  if (val) *val = (unsigned long) v;
1760  return SWIG_OK;
1761  }
1762  /* If v is negative, then this could be a negative number, or an
1763  unsigned value which doesn't fit in a signed long, so try to
1764  get it as a string so we can distinguish these cases. */
1765  }
1766  {
1767  int len = 0;
1768  const char *nptr = Tcl_GetStringFromObj(obj, &len);
1769  if (nptr && len > 0) {
1770  char *endptr;
1771  unsigned long v;
1772  if (*nptr == '-') return SWIG_OverflowError;
1773  errno = 0;
1774  v = strtoul(nptr, &endptr,0);
1775  if (nptr[0] == '\0' || *endptr != '\0')
1776  return SWIG_TypeError;
1777  if (v == ULONG_MAX && errno == ERANGE) {
1778  errno = 0;
1779  return SWIG_OverflowError;
1780  } else {
1781  if (*endptr == '\0') {
1782  if (val) *val = v;
1783  return SWIG_OK;
1784  }
1785  }
1786  }
1787  }
1788 
1789  return SWIG_TypeError;
1790 }

1846 {

1858  if (SWIG_IsOK(res) && val) *val = static_cast< size_t >(v);

2082 SWIGINTERN int
2083 SWIG_AsCharArray(Tcl_Obj * obj, char *val, size_t size)
2084 {
2085  char* cptr = 0; size_t csize = 0; int alloc = SWIG_OLDOBJ;
2086  int res = SWIG_AsCharPtrAndSize(obj, &cptr, &csize, &alloc);
2087  if (SWIG_IsOK(res)) {
2088  /* special case of single char conversion when we don't need space for NUL */
2089  if (size == 1 && csize == 2 && cptr && !cptr[1]) --csize;
2090  if (csize <= size) {
2091  if (val) {
2092  if (csize) memcpy(val, cptr, csize*sizeof(char));
2093  if (csize < size) memset(val + csize, 0, (size - csize)*sizeof(char));
2094  }
2095  if (alloc == SWIG_NEWOBJ) {
2096  delete[] cptr;
2097  res = SWIG_DelNewMask(res);
2098  }
2099  return res;
2100  }
2101  if (alloc == SWIG_NEWOBJ) delete[] cptr;
2102  }
2103  return SWIG_TypeError;
2104 }

2135 /* Getting isfinite working pre C99 across multiple platforms is non-trivial. Users can provide SWIG_isfinite on older platforms. */
2136 #ifndef SWIG_isfinite
2137 /* isfinite() is a macro for C99, but a function in namespace std for C++11. */
2138 # if defined(isfinite)
2139 # define SWIG_isfinite(X) (isfinite(X))
2140 # elif defined __cplusplus && __cplusplus >= 201103L
2141 # define SWIG_isfinite(X) (std::isfinite(X))
2142 # elif defined(_MSC_VER)
2143 # define SWIG_isfinite(X) (_finite(X))
2144 # elif defined(__sun) && defined(__SVR4)
2145 # include <ieeefp.h>
2146 # define SWIG_isfinite(X) (finite(X))
2147 # elif defined(__GNUC__)
2148 # define SWIG_isfinite(X) (__builtin_isfinite(X))
2149 # endif
2150 #endif

16217 #endif
16218 /* -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
16219  * Type initialization:
16220  * This problem is tough by the requirement that no dynamic
16221  * memory is used. Also, since swig_type_info structures store pointers to
16222  * swig_cast_info structures and swig_cast_info structures store pointers back
16223  * to swig_type_info structures, we need some lookup code at initialization.
16224  * The idea is that swig generates all the structures that are needed.
16225  * The runtime then collects these partially filled structures.
16226  * The SWIG_InitializeModule function takes these initial arrays out of
16227  * swig_module, and does all the lookup, filling in the swig_module.types
16228  * array with the correct data and linking the correct swig_cast_info
16229  * structures together.
16230  *
16231  * The generated swig_type_info structures are assigned statically to an initial
16232  * array. We just loop through that array, and handle each type individually.
16233  * First we lookup if this type has been already loaded, and if so, use the
16234  * loaded structure instead of the generated one. Then we have to fill in the
16235  * cast linked list. The cast data is initially stored in something like a
16236  * two-dimensional array. Each row corresponds to a type (there are the same
16237  * number of rows as there are in the swig_type_initial array). Each entry in
16238  * a column is one of the swig_cast_info structures for that type.
16239  * The cast_initial array is actually an array of arrays, because each row has
16240  * a variable number of columns. So to actually build the cast linked list,
16241  * we find the array of casts associated with the type, and loop through it
16242  * adding the casts to the list. The one last trick we need to do is making
16243  * sure the type pointer in the swig_cast_info struct is correct.
16244  *
16245  * First off, we lookup the cast->type name to see if it is already loaded.
16246  * There are three cases to handle:
16247  * 1) If the cast->type has already been loaded AND the type we are adding
16248  * casting info to has not been loaded (it is in this module), THEN we
16249  * replace the cast->type pointer with the type pointer that has already
16250  * been loaded.
16251  * 2) If BOTH types (the one we are adding casting info to, and the
16252  * cast->type) are loaded, THEN the cast info has already been loaded by
16253  * the previous module so we just ignore it.
16254  * 3) Finally, if cast->type has not already been loaded, then we add that
16255  * swig_cast_info to the linked list (because the cast->type) pointer will
16256  * be correct.
16257  * ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
16258 
16259 #ifdef __cplusplus
16260 extern "C" {
16261 #if 0
16262 } /* c-mode */
16263 #endif
16264 #endif
16265 
16266 #if 0
16267 #define SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16268 #endif
16269 
16270 
16271 SWIGRUNTIME void
16272 SWIG_InitializeModule(void *clientdata) {
16273  size_t i;
16274  swig_module_info *module_head, *iter;
16275  int init;
16276 
16277  /* check to see if the circular list has been setup, if not, set it up */
16278  if (swig_module.next==0) {
16279  /* Initialize the swig_module */
16280  swig_module.type_initial = swig_type_initial;
16281  swig_module.cast_initial = swig_cast_initial;
16282  swig_module.next = &swig_module;
16283  init = 1;
16284  } else {
16285  init = 0;
16286  }
16287 
16288  /* Try and load any already created modules */
16289  module_head = SWIG_GetModule(clientdata);
16290  if (!module_head) {
16291  /* This is the first module loaded for this interpreter */
16292  /* so set the swig module into the interpreter */
16293  SWIG_SetModule(clientdata, &swig_module);
16294  } else {
16295  /* the interpreter has loaded a SWIG module, but has it loaded this one? */
16296  iter=module_head;
16297  do {
16298  if (iter==&swig_module) {
16299  /* Our module is already in the list, so there's nothing more to do. */
16300  return;
16301  }
16302  iter=iter->next;
16303  } while (iter!= module_head);
16304 
16305  /* otherwise we must add our module into the list */
16306  swig_module.next = module_head->next;
16307  module_head->next = &swig_module;
16308  }
16309 
16310  /* When multiple interpreters are used, a module could have already been initialized in
16311  a different interpreter, but not yet have a pointer in this interpreter.
16312  In this case, we do not want to continue adding types... everything should be
16313  set up already */
16314  if (init == 0) return;
16315 
16316  /* Now work on filling in swig_module.types */
16317 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16318  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: size %d\n", swig_module.size);
16319 #endif
16320  for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
16321  swig_type_info *type = 0;
16322  swig_type_info *ret;
16323  swig_cast_info *cast;
16324 
16325 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16326  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16327 #endif
16328 
16329  /* if there is another module already loaded */
16330  if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
16331  type = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16332  }
16333  if (type) {
16334  /* Overwrite clientdata field */
16335 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16336  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found type %s\n", type->name);
16337 #endif
16338  if (swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata) {
16339  type->clientdata = swig_module.type_initial[i]->clientdata;
16340 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16341  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found and overwrite type %s \n", type->name);
16342 #endif
16343  }
16344  } else {
16345  type = swig_module.type_initial[i];
16346  }
16347 
16348  /* Insert casting types */
16349  cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
16350  while (cast->type) {
16351  /* Don't need to add information already in the list */
16352  ret = 0;
16353 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16354  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: look cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
16355 #endif
16356  if (swig_module.next != &swig_module) {
16357  ret = SWIG_MangledTypeQueryModule(swig_module.next, &swig_module, cast->type->name);
16358 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16359  if (ret) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: found cast %s\n", ret->name);
16360 #endif
16361  }
16362  if (ret) {
16363  if (type == swig_module.type_initial[i]) {
16364 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16365  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old type %s\n", ret->name);
16366 #endif
16367  cast->type = ret;
16368  ret = 0;
16369  } else {
16370  /* Check for casting already in the list */
16371  swig_cast_info *ocast = SWIG_TypeCheck(ret->name, type);
16372 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16373  if (ocast) printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: skip old cast %s\n", ret->name);
16374 #endif
16375  if (!ocast) ret = 0;
16376  }
16377  }
16378 
16379  if (!ret) {
16380 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16381  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: adding cast %s\n", cast->type->name);
16382 #endif
16383  if (type->cast) {
16384  type->cast->prev = cast;
16385  cast->next = type->cast;
16386  }
16387  type->cast = cast;
16388  }
16389  cast++;
16390  }
16391  /* Set entry in modules->types array equal to the type */
16392  swig_module.types[i] = type;
16393  }
16394  swig_module.types[i] = 0;
16395 
16396 #ifdef SWIGRUNTIME_DEBUG
16397  printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
16398  for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
16399  int j = 0;
16400  swig_cast_info *cast = swig_module.cast_initial[i];
16401  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: type %d %s\n", i, swig_module.type_initial[i]->name);
16402  while (cast->type) {
16403  printf("SWIG_InitializeModule: cast type %s\n", cast->type->name);
16404  cast++;
16405  ++j;
16406  }
16407  printf("---- Total casts: %d\n",j);
16408  }
16409  printf("**** SWIG_InitializeModule: Cast List ******\n");
16410 #endif
16411 }
16412 
16413 /* This function will propagate the clientdata field of type to
16414 * any new swig_type_info structures that have been added into the list
16415 * of equivalent types. It is like calling
16416 * SWIG_TypeClientData(type, clientdata) a second time.
16417 */
16418 SWIGRUNTIME void
16419 SWIG_PropagateClientData(void) {
16420  size_t i;
16421  swig_cast_info *equiv;
16422  static int init_run = 0;
16423 
16424  if (init_run) return;
16425  init_run = 1;
16426 
16427  for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; i++) {
16428  if (swig_module.types[i]->clientdata) {
16429  equiv = swig_module.types[i]->cast;
16430  while (equiv) {
16431  if (!equiv->converter) {
16432  if (equiv->type && !equiv->type->clientdata)
16433  SWIG_TypeClientData(equiv->type, swig_module.types[i]->clientdata);
16434  }
16435  equiv = equiv->next;
16436  }
16437  }
16438  }
16439 }
16440

16442 #if 0
16443 {
16444  /* c-mode */
16445 #endif
16446 }
16447 #endif
16448 
16449 
16450 #ifdef __cplusplus
16451 extern "C" {
16452 #endif

16458  /* Install Constants */
16459 
16460  SWIGINTERN void
16461  SWIG_Tcl_InstallConstants(Tcl_Interp *interp, swig_const_info constants[]) {
16462  size_t i;
16463  Tcl_Obj *obj;
16464 
16465  if (!swigconstTableinit) {
16466  Tcl_InitHashTable(&swigconstTable, TCL_STRING_KEYS);
16467  swigconstTableinit = 1;
16468  }
16469  for (i = 0; constants[i].type; i++) {
16470  switch(constants[i].type) {
16471  case SWIG_TCL_POINTER:
16472  obj = SWIG_NewPointerObj(constants[i].pvalue, *(constants[i]).ptype,0);
16473  break;
16474  case SWIG_TCL_BINARY:
16475  obj = SWIG_NewPackedObj(constants[i].pvalue, constants[i].lvalue, *(constants[i].ptype));
16476  break;
16477  default:
16478  obj = 0;
16479  break;
16480  }
16481  if (obj) {
16482  SWIG_Tcl_SetConstantObj(interp, constants[i].name, obj);
16483  }
16484  }
16485  }
16486 
16487  /* Create fast method lookup tables */
16488 
16489  SWIGINTERN void
16490  SWIG_Tcl_InstallMethodLookupTables(void) {
16491  size_t i;
16492 
16493  for (i = 0; i < swig_module.size; ++i) {
16494  swig_type_info *type = swig_module.type_initial[i];
16495  if (type->clientdata) {
16496  swig_class* klass = (swig_class*) type->clientdata;
16497  swig_method* meth;
16498  Tcl_InitHashTable(&(klass->hashtable), TCL_STRING_KEYS);
16499  for (meth = klass->methods; meth && meth->name; ++meth) {
16500  int newEntry;
16501  Tcl_HashEntry* hashentry = Tcl_CreateHashEntry(&(klass->hashtable), meth->name, &newEntry);
16502  Tcl_SetHashValue(hashentry, (ClientData)meth->method);
16503  }
16504  }
16505  }
16506  }
16507 
16508 #ifdef __cplusplus
16509 }
16510 #endif

16515 
16516 SWIGEXPORT int SWIG_init(Tcl_Interp *interp) {
16517  size_t i;
16518  if (interp == 0) return TCL_ERROR;
16519 #ifdef USE_TCL_STUBS
16520  /* (char*) cast is required to avoid compiler warning/error for Tcl < 8.4. */
16521  if (Tcl_InitStubs(interp, (char*)SWIG_TCL_STUBS_VERSION, 0) == NULL) {
16522  return TCL_ERROR;
16523  }
16524 #endif
16525 #ifdef USE_TK_STUBS
16526  /* (char*) cast is required to avoid compiler warning/error. */
16527  if (Tk_InitStubs(interp, (char*)SWIG_TCL_STUBS_VERSION, 0) == NULL) {
16528  return TCL_ERROR;
16529  }
16530 #endif
16531 
16532  Tcl_PkgProvide(interp, (char*)SWIG_name, (char*)SWIG_version);
16533 
16534 #ifdef SWIG_namespace
16535  Tcl_Eval(interp, "namespace eval " SWIG_namespace " { }");
16536 #endif
16537 
16538  SWIG_InitializeModule((void *) interp);
16539  SWIG_PropagateClientData();
16540 
16541  for (i = 0; swig_commands[i].name; i++) {
16542  Tcl_CreateObjCommand(interp, (char *) swig_commands[i].name, (swig_wrapper_func) swig_commands[i].wrapper,
16543  swig_commands[i].clientdata, NULL);
16544  }
16545  for (i = 0; swig_variables[i].name; i++) {
16546  Tcl_SetVar(interp, (char *) swig_variables[i].name, (char *) "", TCL_GLOBAL_ONLY);
16547  Tcl_TraceVar(interp, (char *) swig_variables[i].name, TCL_TRACE_READS | TCL_GLOBAL_ONLY,
16548  (Tcl_VarTraceProc *) swig_variables[i].get, (ClientData) swig_variables[i].addr);
16549  Tcl_TraceVar(interp, (char *) swig_variables[i].name, TCL_TRACE_WRITES | TCL_GLOBAL_ONLY,
16550  (Tcl_VarTraceProc *) swig_variables[i].set, (ClientData) swig_variables[i].addr);
16551  }
16552 
16553  SWIG_Tcl_InstallConstants(interp, swig_constants);
16554  SWIG_Tcl_InstallMethodLookupTables();
16555
